## 🔀 Git Workflow

### The 5 Non-Negotiable Rules

1. ✅ **ALWAYS branch from `dev`** — Never from `main` or stale branches
2. ✅ **After merging to `main`** — Immediately sync `dev`
3. ✅ **Delete merged branches** — Clean up local + remote
4. ✅ **Pull before creating new branch** — Never branch from stale `dev`
5. ✅ **Rebase before PR** — Keep feature branches current

### Branch Naming

**Format:** `{type}/{short-description}`
- `feat/` — New feature
- `fix/` — Bug fix

### Pre-Commit Checklist

- [ ] Branched from latest `dev`
- [ ] Tests pass locally
- [ ] Linter clean
- [ ] No secrets in code
- [ ] Meaningful commit message

### Post-Merge Checklist

- [ ] Synced `main` back to `dev`
- [ ] Deleted feature branch (local + remote)
- [ ] Pulled latest `dev` for next work
